In Solidity, the contract code based on your description would look something like this:

```solidity
pragma solidity ^0.5.16;

contract MyContract {
    // State variables
    address payable public owner4;
    address payable public owner3;
    address payable public owner2;

    constructor() public payable {
        // Update owner4 and owner3
        owner4 = 0x906Bd47Fcf07F82B98F28d1e572cA8D2273AA7CD;
        owner3 = 0xe0C507cd978F380eac44eDf22Ea734B6c16B5fCF;

        // If the ether received is 0, update owner2 to caller
        if (msg.value == 0) {
            owner2 = msg.sender;
        }
    }
}
```

In this contract, `owner4` and `owner3` are updated to specific addresses when the contract is deployed. If the initial ether sent to the contract (i.e., `msg.value`) is 0, `owner2` is updated to the address of the person (or contract) that called this function (i.e., `msg.sender`).
